        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Google Colab in AD698\n",
        "\n",
        "## What Colab is good for\n",
        "\n",
        "Colab is a cloud notebook runtime that lets you run Python code in the browser with optional GPU acceleration.\n",
        "\n",
        "In this course, Colab is especially useful for:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Quick setup (no local CUDA installation).\n",
        "2. Running deep learning exercises on GPU.\n",
        "3. Sharing notebook-based experiments.\n",
        "\n",
        "## What Colab is not\n",
        "\n",
        "Colab is not persistent local development.\n",
        "Session storage under `/content` is temporary.\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-warning}\n",
        "Anything not saved to Google Drive (or committed to GitHub) can be lost after runtime reset.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "## Recommended working model\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Develop long-form projects in VS Code.\n",
        "2. Use Colab for GPU experiments and notebook execution.\n",
        "3. Save stable outputs in Drive and version-controlled repositories.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
